"/> When my husband and I were first dating, he was late for a date one Saturday.
Turned out that, on the way to my place, he'd seen the car ahead of him hit a cat
and keep going. He slammed on the brakes, pulled over, and went to the cat. It was
clearly dying, but not yet dead. He picked it up, took it to the side of the road,
and held and petted it till it died, and then left a note for its family, should
they find it, to let them know what had happened.

On his way to a hot date with a new chick on a Saturday night, he took the time to
see to it that a cat didn't die alone. It was right then I knew I would love him
till the day that I died.
